   Here is the 59-40 roll call by which the
Senate in effect voted to keep a doubling of the 9-cent-a-gallon
federal gasoline tax in the deficit-reduction bill.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to block the higher
gasoline tax and a ``no'' vote was a vote to keep it in the bill.
   Voting ``yes'' were 14 Democrats and 26 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 41 Democrats and 18 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
